<HEAD>Rapist Sentenced 80 to 160 Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Allegheny County judge has sentenced a
rapist to 80 to 160 years in prison, calling him ``a walking crime
wave.''
   Millard Bowles, 27, of Bethel Park, who stalked women in grocery
store parking lots, was convicted in January of kidnapping two
women at knifepoint and sexually assaulting them in separate
incidents on March 19 and April 7.
   Bowles forced the women to withdraw cash from automated teller
machines after the attacks, police said.
   Despite the brutality of the assaults, Bowles would leave his
telephone number with the victims or try to telephone them later to
arrange another meeting, police said.
   ``Millard Bowles, you are a walking crime wave,'' said Judge
Robert E. Dauer after handing down the sentence Friday. ``I hope
you serve every moment of it.''
