<TEXT>
   A fire in an apartment building early Sunday killed
five people and seriously injured 10, fire officials said.
   The blaze in Paris' 12th district, in the southeast part of the
city, started in a second-floor apartment and spread through the
six-story building via the wooden elevator cage, officials said.
   Up to 100 firefighters battled the flames, containing them in
about an hour, by 6 a.m.
   Five people died in the flames and 10 others suffered burns,
smoke inhalation or fractured bones from jumping from windows,
according to rescue workers.
   About 40 people lived in the building, which was destroyed.
   The cause of the fire was not immediately known.
